      "stem_html": "<p><i>p</i>-Nitrophenol and 2,6-dimethyl-4-nitrophenol both have p<i>K</i><sub>a</sub> = 7.15, but 3,5-dimethyl-4-nitrophenol has p<i>K</i><sub>a</sub> = 8.25. Why is 3,5-dimethyl-4-nitrophenol so much less acidic?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdjhWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--bf451ab1e3fd77c51504a4b618963cae3f173c95/OChem_17_EC_047.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of 4-nitrophenol, 2,6-dimethyl-4-nitrophenol, and 3,5-dimethyl-4-nitrophenol with p K a values 7.15, 7.15, and 8.25, respectively.\">",
